Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to turn. Clay fine pink-buff. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Pencil '29'. Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 44? Name Damophilos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0340.12.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1023)
